  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I believe it is essential.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because unless the viewer of this video knows what is in this, the essence of [INAUDIBLE], they will not understand why the Germans cooperated with us.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I say that the situation is basically different now from the past emigrations which you have shown as it existed in Nazi-- in Germany controlled by the National Socialists.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The overflow by Jewish emigration since 1933 and the likely imminent mass emigration from Spain are causing the countries of the world to tighten their borders, so that the Jews cannot emigrate.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There are essential differences in the need to handle the Jewish emigration for Germany than there were before, the answer was Austria.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The social stratification of Jews in Austria, in Deutsche Osterreich, in German Austria, is very different from the one in the old [NON-ENGLISH], Germany itself.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] In Vienna there are almost 10% of the population Jewish, many of them in leading social positions.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in Germany, they are distributed all over the country.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In Austria they are concentrated almost entirely in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 10 SECONDS] Due to the Anschluss, Germany has become a country of a substantial number of Jews and Jewish inhabitants.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Therefore, the system needs some new organization, some new orientation.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] There is a utilization of related stratification to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "To enter Palestine, you need today a certificate from the British that we are entitled to.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The British hold this number of certificates to a minimum in order to continue to enjoy the favor of the Arabs.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] But from each number of certificates issued-- and this is very important-- a number is retained by the British government for those who entered Palestine without official permission.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
